  "title": "feat(index): accept indexId",
  "body": "The indexid is used in the already existing `getIndexId` function, so all that was needed to be done there was to add a new test to ensure the usage is correct.\r\n\r\nThere can still be conflicts within a scope, but that would be if an indexId is shared\r\n\r\nIFW-930\r\n\r\nI didn't make a story highlighting this use, since it only has an effect in the route state, which isn't yet being listened to for nested indices, so is hard to see in effect for now",
